    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place" rend="right">Washington</name>,
                    <date when="1869-06-12" rend="right">June 12, 1869</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Charles W. Stoddard,</salute>
                <salute>Dear Sir:</salute><ptr target="loc.01685_n1"/>
            </opener>

            <p>Your letters have reached me.<ptr target="loc.01685_n2"/> I cordially accept your appreciation, &amp; reciprocate your friendship. 
                I do not write many letters, but like to meet people. Those tender &amp; primitive personal relations 
                away off there in the Pacific Islands, as described by you, touched me deeply.<ptr target="loc.01685_n3"/>
            </p>
            
            <p>In answer to your request,<ptr target="loc.01685_n4"/> I send you my picture—it was taken three months since. I also send a newspaper.<ptr target="loc.01685_n5"/>
            </p>
            
            <p>Farewell, my friend. I sincerely thank you, &amp; hope some day to meet you.
            </p>

            <closer>
                <signed rend="right">Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer>
        </body>
    </text>
